cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with computer vision models and their vulnerability to distributional shifts, which is a common problem in the field of computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a training procedure to address this vulnerability, which involves optimization and search algorithms, indicating a possible connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper formulates a combinatorial optimization problem, which suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the vulnerability of models to content-preserving image manipulations, which could be related to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
